ans MT'; font-size:11pt">he Association </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt">actively participates in the joint government and industry Construction Leadership Council set up to implement the 2013 Construction Industrial Strategy and actively participate</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt">s</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt"> in the Green Construction Board.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-indent:-28.35pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="2" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 13.31pt; padding-left:15.04pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt">As manufacturers we very much disagree with the omission of any considerations about materials </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt">in t</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt">he proposed new Housing Standards.  We think that a Materials Group should advise on this matter and propose how to take things forward.  </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-indent:-28.35pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="3" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 13.31pt; padding-left:15.04pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt">We support the goal of a low carbon, resource efficient built environment and believe that the construction products sector has a crucial role to play in delivering it.  </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-indent:-28.35pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="4" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 13.31pt; padding-left:15.04pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt">We believe sustainability represents an important business opportunity for UK manufacturers and represents market growth and export potential.  Regulation and Standards are required to drive th</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt">is </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt">forward.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-28.35pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="5" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 13.31pt; padding-left:15.04pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt">Manufacturers want to reduce risk and increase certainty if they are to invest and innovate in new products and solutions.  They therefore w</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt">ant a central s</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt">cheme, a common framework and not a chaos of local inconsistent schemes which would surely arise if left to the marketplace.  Such investment and innovation needs to be rewarded and a means of doing so should be included in the Housing Standards.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-indent:-28.35pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="6" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 13.31pt; padding-left:15.04pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt">We were supporters of the Code for Sustainable Homes (CSH) from the outset and whilst we agree that the CSH had become overly administrative and bureaucratic and more costly than need and was thus ripe for review; it had many good points and these should not be lost within new Housing Standards.  </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt"> What manufacturers want are:</span></li><ol type="a" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 66.98pt; padding-left:5.02pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt">Consistency and standardisation: measure the same things in the same way</span></li><li style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 67.85pt; padding-left:4.15pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt">Building performance focus</span></li><li style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 66.47pt; padding-left:5.53pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt">Performance levels, not simple Pass/Fail</span></li><li style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 67.86pt; padding-left:4.14pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt">To link to direction of future regulation – clarity gives certainty to investment</span></li><li style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 67.14pt; padding-left:4.86pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt">Material credits to remain as market reward for investment in innovation </span></li></ol></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 35.45pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="7" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 31.86pt; padding-left:4.14pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt">The Code for Sustainable Homes provided these characteristics; if these are omitted from the Housing Standards then our sector fears a chao</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt">tic and thus costly marketplace </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt">for manufacturers.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="8" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 31.86pt; padding-left:4.14pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt">We would be happy to liaise further with your Committee if this would be helpful.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">3 October 2013</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="color:#000080; font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:5.5pt; font-weight:bold; letter-spacing:1.15pt; text-decoration:none">              </span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="color:#000080; font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:5.5pt; letter-spacing:2pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="color:#000080; font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:5.5pt">&#xa0;</span></p></div></body></html>